Here is an example PHP script that integrates with the Slack API to send notifications when a new user signs up:

<?php

// Set the Slack webhook URL and channel name
$slack_webhook_url = "https://hooks.slack.com/services/XXXXX/XXXXX/XXXXXXXXXX";
$slack_channel = "#notifications";

// Get the user's information from the database
$user_id = $_POST['user_id'];
$user_name = $_POST['user_name'];
$user_email = $_POST['user_email'];

// Format the message for Slack
$message = "New user registered:\n"
$message .= "Name: $user_name\n"
$message .= "Email: $user_email\n"

// Prepare the payload for the Slack API
$payload = array(
    'channel' => $slack_channel,
    'username' => 'My Web App',
    'text' => $message,
    'icon_emoji' => ':rocket:'
);

// Send the payload to the Slack webhook URL
$ch = curl_init($slack_webhook_url);
curl_setopt($ch, CURLOPT_CUSTOMREQUEST, "POST");
curl_setopt($ch, CURLOPT_POSTFIELDS, json_encode($payload));
curl_setopt($ch, CURLOPT_RETURNTRANSFER, true);
curl_setopt($ch, CURLOPT_HTTPHEADER, array('Content-Type: application/json'));
$result = curl_exec($ch);
curl_close($ch);

// Check for errors and display a message
if (!$result) {
    echo "Failed to send notification to Slack!";
} else {
    echo "Notification sent successfully!";
}

?>

This script assumes that the user's information is passed to the script in a POST request with the variables user_id, user_name, and user_email. You would need to modify this script to fit the specific requirements of your web application and database schema. Additionally, you would need to replace the webhook URL and channel name with your own values.

The script first prepares the message to be sent to Slack by formatting the user's information in a clear and concise way. It then prepares a payload array with the necessary data for the Slack API, including the channel name, username, message, and icon. Finally, the script sends the payload to the Slack webhook URL using CURL and checks for any errors before displaying a success or failure message to the user.
